	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 22nd 12:29 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off Monks are not tanks, so although you want high AC/HP this will never be your strength.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monks are best at not being hit, period. AGI is the stat that facilitates this. High AGI will allow your monk to be missed in combat more, thereby rendering less need for high AC/HP. Don't misunderstand me though, being a melee character, Monks will still be hit in combat often so the need for AC/HP are still there, just less than perhaps a warrior. But then again the Warriors job is to be the meat shield, the Monk however, is designed to have the highest output of damage in melee combat.<br>As far as stats go STR, AGI, DEX are what you want to concentrate on in that respective order IMHO. Being an offensive juggernaught, you can see how STR would be useful for adding more damage in combat, AGI for the Monkly defensive capabilities and DEX for procs on higher end weapons. Of course you can choose one stat and go overboard as many do but IMHO being diversified is always the way to go. My human monk, Anuki on Rallos, has these base stas: 90 STR  90 AGI  90 DEX, the rest I forget as they are of no consequense. Also there are many items with wich to tweak your stats so dont be too quick to trash your first monk unless you put your points into wisdom or something rediculous...<br>Also btw you cannot use 1HB and 2HB at the same time to increase skills... 2HB is just that... weapons requiring 2 hands to weild! Alternate between weapons though when they are maxed out for that level and resist the urge to keep using the best weapon... always keep your options open my friend. Oh you mentioned the AC penalty for being over 14 lbs also... this is crucial at higher levels... your AC will plummet badly so watch carefully what gear you wear. Acquire a large sewing kit to store goods in until you get your hands on weight reducing bags, just be wary of the COMBINE button! lol Anyway I hope this helps some... keep at your monk they are an extremely fun class to play with awesome fighting moves that are always a blast to watch. They are the best pullers, do the most melee damage, are cheap to play not requiring uber gear to function well, and are highly sought after in high level raids. Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
